{"parse":{"title":"flow","pageid":8443,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfləʊ̯/|[ˈfləʊ̯]|;|/ˈflɵʊ̯/|[ˈflɵ̞ʊ̯]|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-flow.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfloʊ̯/|[ˈfloʊ̯]|;|/ˈflɔʊ̯/|[ˈflɔʊ̯]|a=GA,[[w:Standard Canadian English|Standard Canadian]]}}\n** {{audio|en|En-us-flow.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈfləʉ̯/|[ˈfləʉ̯]|;|/ˈflɘʉ̯/|[ˈflɘ̞ʉ̯]|;|/ˈflɐʉ̯/|[ˈflɐ̝ʉ̯]|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{rhymes|en|əʊ|s=1}}\n* {{hmp|en|floe|Flo}}\n* {{hyph|en|flow}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|flowe}}, from the verb (see below). The psychology sense “state of focus” was {{coin|en|Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi|in=1975|nocap=1|nocat=1}}.\n[[File:Jõelähtme_jõgi._01.jpg|thumb|]]\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# Movement in people or things characterized with a continuous motion, involving either a non solid mass or a multitude.\n# The movement of a [[real]] or [[figurative]] [[fluid]].\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|IV|48|Mr. Cooke at once began a tirade against the residents of Asquith for permitting a sandy and generally disgraceful condition of the roads. So roundly did he vituperate the inn management in particular, and with such a loud '''flow''' of words, that I trembled lest he should be heard on the veranda.}}\n# {{lb|en|math}} A [[formalization]] of the idea of the [[motion]] of [[particle]]s in a [[fluid]], as a [[group]] [[action]] of the [[real number]]s on a [[set]].\n#: {{uxa|en|The notion of '''flow''' is basic to the study of ordinary differential equations.}}\n# The rising movement of the [[tide]].\n# [[smoothness|Smoothness]] or [[continuity]].\n#: {{uxa|en|The room was small, but it had good symmetry and '''flow'''.}}\n# The amount of a fluid that moves or the rate of fluid movement.\n#: {{uxa|en|Turn on the valve and make sure you have sufficient '''flow'''.}}\n#: {{uxa|en|Other devices measure water '''flow''' in streams fed by melted ice.}}\n# A flow pipe, carrying liquid away from a boiler or other central plant (compare with [[return]] pipe which returns fluid to central plant).\n# {{sid|en|mental state}} {{lb|en|psychology}} A mental state characterized by [[concentration]], [[focus]]{{,}} and enjoyment of a given task.\n#* {{quote-web|en|url=http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/the-running-blog/2014/jan/14/achieve-state-flow-running-perform-best|title=How to achieve a state of flow when running|date=2014-01-14|author=Alex Lockwood|work=The Guardian|passage=The point about '''flow''' is that it is enjoyable. As research has shown \"the more often athletes experienced '''flow''', the happier they were.\" But the second is that entering '''flow''' actually improves performance.}}\n# The [[emission]] of [[blood]] during [[menstruation]].\n#: {{uxa|en|Tampons can be small or large, slender or thick. From “slender” to “super”, you can pick the size that matches your '''flow'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|rap|_|music|_|jargon}} The ability to skillfully [[rap]] along to a [[beat]].\n#: {{uxa|en|The production on his new mixtape is mediocre but his '''flow''' is on point.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|title=w:In da Club|artist=w:50 Cent|year=2003|album=Get Rich or Die Tryin'|passage=Now shawty said she feelin' my style, she feelin' my '''flow''' {{...}} / My '''flow''', my show brought me the dough / That bought me all my fancy things}}\n# {{lb|en|software}} The sequence of steps taken in a piece of [[software]] to perform some action.\n#: {{coa|en|login '''flow'''}}\n#: {{coa|en|search '''flow'''}}\n#* {{quote-mailing list|en|year=2015|author=Dan|list=snowplow-user|title=Best practices for tracking progress through a sign up flow|url=https://groups.google.com/g/snowplow-user/c/dywzOftTC6g/m/sx-Ij16FCAAJ|text=I'm setting up event tracking for a pretty standard, multi-step signup '''flow''', and I'm wondering [...]}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|continuity}} See also [[Thesaurus:continuity]]\n\n=====Antonyms=====\n* {{antsense|movement of the tide}} {{l|en|ebb}}\n* {{antsense|continuity}} See also [[Thesaurus:discontinuity]]\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n{{col|en\n|airflow\n|antiflow\n|control flow\n|dark flow\n|deal flow\n|downflow\n|inflow\n|inviscid flow\n|irrotational flow\n|lava flow\n|midflow\n|non-Newtonian flow\n|onflow\n|outflow\n|overflow\n|postflow\n|preflow\n|reflow\n|subflow\n|upflow\n}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|adjusted flow time\n|aflow\n|afterflow\n|air flow\n|ashflow\n|autoflow\n|backflow\n|baseflow\n|blood flow\n|byflow\n|cash flow\n|cerebral blood flow\n|coflow\n|conflow\n|contraflow\n|control-flow graph\n|counterflow\n|crossflow\n|data flow\n|data flow diagram\n|earthflow\n|ebb and flow\n|Fanno flow\n|floodflow\n|flowability\n|flowage\n|flowant\n|flow art\n|flow arts\n|flow battery\n|flow blue\n|flow cell\n|flowchart\n|flow chart\n|flow control\n|flow cytometer\n|flowcytometric\n|flow cytometry\n|flow diagram\n|flower\n|flow field\n|flowgram\n|flowgraph\n|flowgraphy\n|flowless\n|flowlike\n|flowline\n|flowmap\n|flowmeter\n|flowmetric\n|flowmotion\n|flow motion\n|flow network\n|flow-on\n|flow-on effect\n|flow on effect\n|flowpath\n|flow production\n|flow rate\n|flowrate\n|flow sheet\n|flowsheet\n|flowsnake\n|flow state\n|flowstone\n|flow stress\n|flowthrough\n|flowtime\n|flowtop\n|flow tracer\n|flow variable\n|flowy\n|foreflow\n|free cash flow\n|freeflow\n|gene flow\n|geneflow\n|go with the flow\n|go with the flow of traffic\n|grainflow\n|Hubble flow\n|hyperflow\n|hyperpycnal flow\n|in flow<l:poker>\n|in full flow\n|interflow\n|isentropic flow\n|isocratic flow\n|jet flow\n|Knudsen flow\n|laminar flow\n|laminar flow hood\n|lateral flow test\n|lineflow\n|mass flow\n|microflow\n|mindflow\n|mudflow\n|multiflow\n|nanoflow\n|newsflow\n|nonflow\n|off-flow\n|only dead fish go with the flow\n|overflow\n|page flow\n|peak flow\n|peak flow meter\n|plastic flow\n|pyroclastic flow\n|rainflow\n|return flow\n|Ricci flow\n|semiflow\n|sheet flow\n|single-flow\n|slushflow\n|stemflow\n|stormflow\n|streamflow\n|superflow\n|throughflow\n|transverse flow effect\n|turbulent flow\n|uniflow\n|uroflow\n|wake flow\n|waterflow\n|water flow\n|wordflow\n|workflow\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|the movement of a fluid}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|rrjedhje}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|агыш}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|تَدَفُّق|m}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|հոսք}}, {{t+|hy|հոսանք}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|fluxu|m}}, {{t|ast|fluxu|m}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|etorri}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|цячэ́нне|n}}, {{t|be|плынь|f}}, {{t|be|пато́к|m}}\n* Blackfoot: {{t|bla|áwa'kimsska}}\n* Breton: {{t|br|beradur|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|тече́ние|n}}, {{t+|bg|пото́к|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|flux|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|流}}\n* Chuvash: {{t|cv|юх}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|tok|m}}, {{t|cs|proudění|n}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|strøm|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|stroom}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|fluo}}, {{t|eo|alfluo}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|vool}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|virtaus}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|écoulement|m}}, {{t+|fr|flux}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|fluxo|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|დინება}}, {{t|ka|დენა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Fluss|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ροή|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ῥεῦμα|n}}, {{t|grc|ῥοία|f}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|प्रवाह|m}}, {{t+|hi|बहाव|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|áramlás}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|alir}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|sreabh|f}}, {{t|ga|sileadh|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|flusso|m}}, {{t+|it|colata|f}}, {{t+|it|scorrimento|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|流れ|tr=ながれ, nagare}}\n* Karachay-Balkar: {{t|krc|агъым}}\n* Kashubian: {{t|csb|cec}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|흐름}}\n* Latgalian: {{t|ltg|tekme}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|fluxus}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|plūsma|f}}\n* Luhya: {{t|luy|omuhula}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|тек|m}}, {{t|mk|тече́ние|n}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|वाहने}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|урсгал}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|no|flom|m}}, {{t+|no|strøm|m}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Fluss|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|przepływ|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fluxo|m}}, {{t+|pt|escoamento|m}}, {{t+|pt|caudal|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|curgere|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|тече́ние|n}}, {{t+|ru|пото́к|m}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|रेतस्|n}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|то̑к|m}}, {{t|sh|тѐче̄ње|n}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|tȏk|m}}, {{t+|sh|tèčēnje|n}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|flussu|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|prúd|m}}, {{t|sk|tok|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|tok|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|flujo|m}}\n* Sundanese: {{t|su|kucur}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|mkondo}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ström|c}}, {{t+|sv|flöde|n}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஓட்டம்}}\n* Tatar: {{t+|tt|агыш}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|ప్రవాహము}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|akış}}, {{t+|tr|seyelan}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|سیلان|tr=seyelân}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|течі́я|f}}, {{t|uk|те́ча|f}}, {{t|uk|плин|m}}, {{t|uk|плив|m}}, {{t+|uk|поті́к|m}}, {{t|uk|струм|m}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|oqim}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|dòng chảy}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|the rising movement of the tide}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|մակընթացություն}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|fluxu|m}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|lanv|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|прили́в|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|flux|m}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|příliv|m}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|flod}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|vloed}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|alfluo}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|tõus}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|vuoksi}}, {{t+|fi|nousuvesi}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|flux|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Flut|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πλημμυρίδα|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|ár|id=flood}}, {{t+|hu|áradás}}, {{t+|hu|dagály}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|riflusso|n}}, {{t+|it|flusso|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|при́лив|m}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|fllot}}\n* Norwegian: {{t+|no|flo|f|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|przypływ|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[fluxo]] [[da]] [[maré]]}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|flux|n}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|прили́в|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|lìonadh|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|príliv|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|flujo|m}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|mkondo}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஓதம்}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|met}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|smoothness or continuity}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|rrjedhë}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|плавност|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|flux|m}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|afronding}}, {{t+|nl|ronding}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|sujuvus}}, {{t|et|ladusus}} {{qualifier|speech}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|fluidità|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fluidez|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|пла́вность|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|flujo|m}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|mkondo}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|தொடர்}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|yurum}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|rate of fluid movement}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|дебит|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|cabal|m}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|debiet}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|vool}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|virtaama}}, {{t+|fi|virtaus}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|παροχή|f}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|aliran}}, {{t+|id|debit}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|flusso|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|про́ток|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|przepływ|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fluxo|m}}, {{t+|pt|caudal|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|caudal|m}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஓட்டம்}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|being at one with}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-check|bg|съсредоточение|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|een zijn met}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|ykseys}}\n* German: {{t|de|Tätigkeitsrausch}}\n* Greek: {{t|el|είμαι ένα με}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|вовлечённость|f}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|-ஓடு}}, {{t+|ta|ஒன்றாக}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|dever|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====Further reading=====\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{pedia|Flow (psychology)}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|en|etymverb}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|flowen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|flōwan|t=to flow}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*flōan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*flōaną|t=to flow}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*plōw-}}, lengthened ''o''-{{glossary|grade}} form of {{m|ine-pro|*plew-|t=to fly, flow, run}}. \n\nCognate with {{cog|stq|flouje|t=to flow}}, {{cog|fy|floeie|t=to flow}}, {{cog|nl|vloeien|t=to flow}}, {{cog|no|flo|t=to flow}}. Compare also {{cog|en|float}}. Not cognate with {{noncog|la|fluō}} despite similarity.\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To move as a [[fluid]] from one position to another.\n#: {{uxa|en|Rivers '''flow''' from springs and lakes.}}\n#: {{uxa|en|Tears '''flow''' from the eyes.}}\n#* {{quote-video game|en|developer=w:BioWare|title={{w|Mass Effect (video game)|Mass Effect}}|location=Redwood City|publisher=Electronic Arts|year=2008|genre=[[science fiction|Science Fiction]]|system=PC|scene=|isbn=9780784546642|oclc=246633669|passage={{w|Wrex}}: I need to get my blood '''flowing'''. Find me something to kill!}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[proceed]]; to [[issue]] [[forth]]; to [[emanate]].\n#: {{uxa|en|Wealth '''flows''' from industry and economy.}}\n#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Lost|book=VII|217|signature=Ee|verso=yes|lines=1238{{ndash}}1239|Tho{{long s}}e thou{{long s}}and decencies that daily '''flow''' ¶ From all her words and actions, mixt with Love}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To move or match smoothly, gracefully, or continuously.\n#: {{uxa|en|The writing is grammatically correct, but it just doesn't '''flow'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Dryden Aeneis||chapter=Dedication|183|{{...|But}}''Virgil'',{{...|who never attempted the Lyrick Ver{{long s}}e,}}is{{...|every where Elegant,}}{{long s}}weet and '''flowing''' in his ''Hexameters''.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To have or be in abundance; to abound, so as to run or flow over.\n#* {{RQ:KJV|Joel|3|18|18|signature=Ffff3|verso=yes|page=969|columns=1{{ndash}}2|{{...|¶ And it {{long s}}hall come to pa{{long s}}{{long s}}e}}in that day, ''that''{{...|the mountaines shal drop downe new wine, and}}the hils {{long s}}hall '''flow''' with milke,{{...|and all the riuers of Iudah {{long s}}hall flow with waters, and}}a fountaine {{long s}}hall come forth of the hou{{long s}}e of the {{smc|Lord}},{{nb...|and {{long s}}hall water the valley of Shittim.}}|“In that day{{...|the mountains will drip new wine, and}}the hills will '''flow''' with milk;{{...|all the ravines of Judah will run with water.}}A fountain will flow out of the Lord’s house{{nb...|and will water the valley of acacias. {{sqbrace|Or ''Valley of Shittim''}}}}|version=NIV}}\n#* {{RQ:Wilson Burns|passage=the exhilaration of a night that needed not the influence of the '''flowing''' bowl}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To hang loosely and wave.\n#: {{coa|en|a '''flowing''' mantle}}\n#: {{coa|en|'''flowing''' locks}}\n#* {{RQ:Federalist|LXVII|Concerning the Con{{long s}}titution of the Pre{{long s}}ident: A gro{{long s}}s Attempt to mi{{long s}}repre{{long s}}ent this Part of the Plan detected.|222|{{...|He has been {{long s}}hewn to us with the diadem {{long s}}parkling on his brow, and}}the imperial purple '''flowing''' in his train.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[rise]], as the [[tide]]; opposed to ''[[ebb]]''.\n#: {{syn|en|come in|come up}}\n#: {{uxa|en|The tide '''flows''' twice in twenty-four hours.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 4-2|IV|iv|93|2|line=125|The Riuer hath thrice '''flow’d''', no ebbe betweene:|The river hath thrice '''flow’d''', no ebb between;}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|computing}} To arrange (text in a wordprocessor, etc.) so that it wraps neatly into a designated space; to [[reflow]].\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To allow (a liquid) to flow.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1932|author=Carl Ernest Reistle|title=Paraffin and Congealing-Oil Problems|volume=340-349|page=45\n|passage=The action is usually progressive, and as a certain amount of oil is '''flowed''' from the tubing it lowers the pressure on the remaining oil and liberates more gas, thus causing additional oil to flow from the tubing.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cover with [[water]] or other [[liquid]]; to [[overflow]]; to [[inundate]]; to [[flood]].\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cover with [[varnish]].\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[discharge]] [[excessive]] [[blood]] from the [[uterus]].\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|flowable,reflowable\n|flow out\n|free-flowing\n|full-flowing\n|get one's juices flowing\n|overflow\n|underflow\n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to move as a fluid}}\n* Acehnese: {{t|ace|ile}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|vloei}}, {{t+|af|stroom}}, {{t+|af|loop}}\n* Aklanon: {{t|akl|ilog}}, {{t|akl|sueog}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|rrjedh}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|агар}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|ተትረፈረፈ}}\n* Andi: {{t|ani|чвахуниду}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|تَدَفَّقَ}}, {{t|ar|سَالَ}}\n* Aragonese: {{t-needed|an}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|հոսել}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|cur}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|বোৱা}}, {{t|as|বৈ যোৱা}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|afluyir}}, {{t+|ast|afluir}}\n* Avar: {{t|av|чвахизе}}\n* Aymara: {{t-needed|ay}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|axmaq}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|ағыу}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|цячы́|impf}}\n* Bengali: {{t|bn|প্রবাহিত হওয়া}}\n* Breton: {{t|br|deverañ}}, {{t+|br|berañ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|тека}}, {{t|bg|лея се}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|စီး}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|fluir}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|流}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|流}}\n* Choctaw: {{t|cho|yʋnʋlli}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|frosa}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|téct}}, {{t+|cs|proudit}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|strømme}}\n* Dhivehi: {{t-needed|dv}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|vloeien}}, {{t+|nl|stromen}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|flui}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|voolama}}\n* Even: {{t|eve|эендэй}}\n* Evenki: {{t|evn|эендеми}}\n* Ewe: {{t-needed|ee}}\n* Extremaduran: {{t|ext|correl}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|floyma}}, {{t+|fo|streyma}}, {{t+|fo|renna}}\n* Fijian: {{t+|fj|kui}}, {{t|fj|sali}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|virrata}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|couler}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|scori}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|fluír}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|დინება}}, {{t|ka|დენა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|fließen}}, {{t+|de|rinnen}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ρέω}}, {{t+|el|κυλώ}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ῥέω}}\n* Gujarati: {{t-needed|gu}}\n* Hausa: {{t-needed|ha}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|kahe}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|זרם|tr=zarám}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|बहना}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|folyik}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|renna}}, {{t+|is|streyma}}, {{t+|is|flæða}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|fluar}}\n* Igbo: {{t-needed|ig}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|alur}}, {{t+|id|alir}}, {{t+|id|salur}}, {{t+|id|salir}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|vallua}}, {{t|izh|virrata}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|fluer}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|sreabh}}, {{t|ga|snigh}}\n*: Old Irish: {{t|sga|snigid}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|fluire}}, {{t+|it|scorrere}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|ながれる|tr=ながれる, nagareru|alt=流れる}}\n* Javanese: {{t|jv|kocor}}, {{t+|jv|mili}}\n*: Old Javanese: {{t|kaw|ili}}\n* Kannada: {{t-needed|kn}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|ហូរ|tr=hoa}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|흐르다}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ໄຫຼ}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|fluō}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|bė́gti}}, {{t|lt|tekė́ti}}\n* Lü: {{t|khb|ᦺᦜ}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|fléissen}}\n* Malay:\n*: Jawi: {{t+|ms|الور}}, {{t|ms|الير}}, {{t|ms|سالور}}, {{t|ms|سالير}}\n*: Rumi: {{t+|ms|alur}}, {{t|ms|alir}}, {{t+|ms|salur}}, {{t+|ms|salir}}\n* Malayalam: {{t-needed|ml}}\n* Manchu: {{t|mnc|ᡝᠶᡝᠮᠪᡳ}}\n* Manx: {{t|gv|sheel}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|tahe}}, {{t|mi|pūheke}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|वाहने}}, {{t|mr|वाहने}}\n* Marshallese: {{t|mh|ae}}\n* Mirandese: {{t-needed|mwl}}\n* Mongolian: {{t+|mn|цутгах}}\n* Nanai: {{t|gld|хэе-}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|nílį́}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|flomme}}, {{t|no|strømme}}, {{t|no|fløda}}, {{t|no|fløyma}}\n* Odia: {{t-needed|or}}\n* Old Church Slavonic:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|cu|тещи|impf}}\n* Old East Slavic: {{t|orv|течи|impf}}\n* Pashto: {{t-needed|ps}}\n* Persian: {{t-needed|fa}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|płynąć}}, {{t+|pl|przepływać}}, {{t+|pl|ciec|impf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fluir}}\n* Punjabi: {{t-needed|pa}}\n* Rarotongan: {{t|rar|ta‘e}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|curge}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|fluir}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|течь|impf}}, {{t+|ru|струи́ться|impf}}\n* Samoan: {{t|sm|tafe}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|स्रवति}}, {{t+|sa|प्रवहति}}\n* Sardinian: {{t-needed|sc}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|sruth}}, {{t|gd|sil}}, {{t|gd|ruith}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t|sh|teći}}, {{t|sh|тећи}}\n* Shan: {{t+|shn|လႆ}}\n* Sicilian: {{t-needed|scn}}\n* Sindhi: {{t-needed|sd}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|ගලා යාම}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|tiecť}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|teči}}\n* Somali: {{t-needed|so}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|běžaś|impf}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|fluir}}\n* Sundanese: {{t|su|kucur}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|strömma}}, {{t+|sv|flyta}}\n* Tabaru: {{t|tby|uisi}}\n* Tahitian: {{t|ty|tahe}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|ஓடு}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|ప్రవహించు}}, {{t+|te|పారు}}\n* Tetum: {{t|tet|suli}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ไหล}}\n* Tooro: {{t|ttj|gera|alt=-gera}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|akmak}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|акмак}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|текти́|impf}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|بہنا|tr=bahnā}}\n* Uyghur: {{t-needed|ug}}\n* Uzbek: {{t|uz|оқмоқ}}\n* Venetan: {{t|vec|scórare}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|chảy}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|flumön}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|cori}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|llifo}}\n* Wolof: {{t-needed|wo}}\n* Xhosa: {{t-needed|xh}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|פֿליסן}}\n* Yoruba: {{t-needed|yo}}\n* Zealandic: {{t|zea|stroôme}}\n* Zulu: {{t|zu|goboza}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to move smoothly}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|vloei}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|тека}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|sujua}}, {{t+|fi|soljua}}, {{t+|fi|lipua}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ρέω}}, {{t+|el|κυλώ}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|scorrere}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|tuanaki}}, {{t|mi|kaunuku}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to come in as the tide}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|приливам|impf}}, {{t|bg|прилея|pf}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|rifluire}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|pākato}}, {{t|mi|pari}}, {{t|mi|heru}}, {{t|mi|kato}}\n* Marshallese: {{t|mh|ibwij}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* French: {{qualifier|used more for spurt}} {{t+check|fr|jaillir}}\n* Ido: {{t+check|io|fluar}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t-check|sh|те̏ћи}}\n*: Latin: {{t-check|sh|tȅći}}\n* Telugu: {{t+check|te|ప్రవహించు}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{unc|en}}. Perhaps from {{cog|non|flói|t=a large bay, firth}}, see {{m|en|floe}}. Compare {{cog|sco|flow|t=peat-bog, marsh}}, {{cog|is|flói|t=marshy ground}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Scotland}} A [[bog]] or [[mire]], especially a rough, waterlogged one.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1794|author=John Sinclair|title=The Statistical Account of Scotland|volume=10|page=328\n|passage={{...}} there are other extensive mosses in this district, commonly called flowes, which it is not probable ever will, or ever can be, converted into arable land. Some of these '''flowes''' are found to be 20, 25, or 30 feet deep, and are, besides, such a dead level, that the water has little or no descent; and even supposing they should be cast, or burnt to the bottom, standing pools of dirty water could only stand in their place.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1871|author=Alexander Boswell|title=Poetical Works|page=213\n|passage=Ye'll stick in some '''flow''', Or, ye'll melt in a thow}}\n#* '''1895''', Crockett, ''Moss-Hags'' page xlii:\n#*: Had been roughly laid with bog-wood dug from the '''flowes''',\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1896|author=Proudlock|title=Borderland Muse|page=8\n|passage=Dandering o'er ferney knowes, [...] Springing o'er bogs an' '''flowes''', [...]}}\n#* '''1898''' July 23, ''Shetland News'', quoted in the ''EDD'':\n#*: If dey wirna a day apo' da '''flow''' dan he [it] wis nae man's bishaness.\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* [[flow-bog]], [[flow-moss]]\n\n====References====\n* {{R:OED Online|flow|n.{{sup|2}}|71999}}\n* {{R:DSL|entry=flow|pos=v., n.{{sup|1}}|noformat=yes|url=http://www.dsl.ac.uk/entry/snd/flow_v_n1}}\n* {{R:EDD|flow}} (suggests the origin is Norwegian dialectal ''floe'' \"pool of water in swampy ground; swamp\")\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=flow|Wolf|fowl|wolf}}\n\n{{C|en|Liquids|Wetlands}}\n\n==Dutch==\n{{wp|nl:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/floː/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-flow.ogg}}\n* {{hyph|nl|flow}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{ety|nl|:ubor|en:flow}}\n{{ubor|nl|en|flow}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|f,m|-s|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|music}} [[rhythm]], {{l|en|flow}} of music (particularly in jazz)\n#: {{uxa|nl|Het duurde een paar nummers, maar toen de drummer eenmaal op gang kwam kreeg Baba Commandant de '''flow''' die essentieel is in afrobeat.|It took a few songs, but once the drummer got going, Baba Commandant got the '''rhythm''' that is essential in Afrobeat.}}\n# {{lb|nl|music}} {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|ability to skilfully rap}}\n#: {{uxa|nl|Snoop rapt met zijn vertrouwd achteloze '''flow'''.|Snoop raps with his familiar casual '''flow'''.}}\n# {{lb|nl|psychology}} {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|mental state characterized by concentration, focus{{,}} and enjoyment of a given task}}\n#: {{uxa|nl|Je lichaam maakt onder stress extra adrenaline aan, waardoor je in een '''flow''' raakt. Dat kan goed zijn voor je concentratie.|Your body produces extra adrenaline under stress, which puts you in a '''flow'''. This can be good for your concentration.}}\n# [[streak]] of successes\n#: {{uxa|nl|Roger Federer verloor op de Australian Open kansloos van Novak Djokovic. De '''flow''' die de Zwitser ooit had lijkt doorbroken.|Roger Federer lost to Novak Djokovic at the Australian Open without a chance. The '''streak''' that the Swiss once had seems to have been broken.}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|flowen||bare-verb}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:nl:Woordenlijst}}\n\n==French==\n{{wp|fr:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:ubor|en:flow}}\n{{ubor|fr|en|flow}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|flo}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-flow.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-flow.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-flow.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n* {{hyph|fr|flow}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|music}} {{l|en|flow}}\n# {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|style}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pl|etydate=|tree=1|text=*|:ubor|en:flow}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|floł,flo|h=flow}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-in,n|indecl=1}} {{tlb|pl|colloquial|uncountable}}\n\n# {{lb|pl|rap|_|music|_|jargon}} {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|the ability to skillfully rap along to a beat}}\n# {{senseid|pl|Q750449}} {{lb|pl|psychology}} {{l|en|flow|id=mental state}} {{gl|a mental state characterized by concentration, focus{{,}} and enjoyment of a given task}}\n#: {{syn|pl|przepływ}}\n#: {{coa|pl|złapać '''flow'''|to catch '''flow'''}}\n# {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|smoothness or continuity}}\n#: {{uxa|pl|Czy był '''flow''' na callu?|Was there good '''flow''' on the call?}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=verbs|mieć flow<g:impf>}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|pl|title=nouns|cash flow}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n* {{R:pl:OJUW}}\n* {{R:pl:OJUW3}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n{{wp|pt:Flow (rap)}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pt|text=*|:ubor|en:flow}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|flow}}\n{{rfap|pt}}\n* {{hyph|pt|flow}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|flows}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|colloquial}} {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|the ability to [[rap]] skillfully}}\n\n==Spanish==\n{{wp|es:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|es|:ubor|en:flow}}\n{{ubor|es|en|flow}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|flou<hyph:flow>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|es|colloquial}} {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|the ability to [[rap]] skillfully}}\n# {{lb|es|colloquial|uncommon}} {{l|en|flow}} {{gl|as in {{m|en|go with the flow}}}}\n#: {{coa|es|ir con el '''flow'''|[[go with the flow|go with the '''flow''']]}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{U:es:unadapted}}"}}